  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WFP&apos;s activities in relation to the conflict in Syria, 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rising fuel costs, drought, international sanctions and destroyed food production causes low food security in many parts of Syria. According to WFP 9,8 mio. people live in food insecurity. WFP aims at delivering food assistance to 4,5 mio. people inside Syria + 2.1 mio. people living in neighbouring states. WFP has targeted its work to refugees with critical needs through the application of a range of criteria selecting recipients. WFP has already had to reduce its planned food assistance to Turkey due to limited financing.</narrative>
  </description>
